Genetic Algorithms. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of Genetic Algorithms (GAs) in solving problems based on the Building-Block Hypothesis, which involves decomposing problems into sub-solutions and assembling them. The paper proposes a model of hierarchical interdependency between building-blocks that can be applied consistently through multiple levels, and presents empirical results of GAs on a canonical example of this model. The paper does not discuss any other sub-category of AI.
